[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 6.514,
        "duration": 1.152
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 7.666,
        "duration": 2.915
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the cookie dough.",
        "start": 23.112,
        "duration": 2.635
    },
    {
        "text": "Whip the butter in a bowl ",
        "start": 26.565,
        "duration": 1.551
    },
    {
        "text": "with a hand-mixer until creamy.",
        "start": 28.116,
        "duration": 3.267
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the extra fine sugar and mix.",
        "start": 36.036,
        "duration": 3.171
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn on the mixer ",
        "start": 44.543,
        "duration": 1.467
    },
    {
        "text": "and whip until it lightens in color.",
        "start": 46.01,
        "duration": 3.103
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the beaten egg a little at a time ",
        "start": 50.412,
        "duration": 2.74
    },
    {
        "text": "while mixing.",
        "start": 53.152,
        "duration": 1.7
    },
    {
        "text": "If the egg and butter separate, ",
        "start": 55.089,
        "duration": 2.094
    },
    {
        "text": "try adding a small amount of the cake flour.",
        "start": 57.183,
        "duration": 3.406
    },
    {
        "text": "This may fix the separation ",
        "start": 60.751,
        "duration": 2.018
    },
    {
        "text": "but be sure not to use ",
        "start": 62.769,
        "duration": 1.501
    },
    {
        "text": "more than the total amount of flour later.",
        "start": 64.27,
        "duration": 3.385
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the vanilla extract and continue to mix.",
        "start": 68.976,
        "duration": 3.697
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, in a mesh strainer, ",
        "start": 80.426,
        "duration": 2.184
    },
    {
        "text": "combine the cake flour, ",
        "start": 82.61,
        "duration": 2.068
    },
    {
        "text": "almond powder ",
        "start": 87.047,
        "duration": 1.639
    },
    {
        "text": "and a pinch of salt.",
        "start": 90.764,
        "duration": 1.753
    },
    {
        "text": "Sieve the powder into the bowl.",
        "start": 94.458,
        "duration": 2.509
    },
    {
        "text": "Combine the mixture with a rubber spatula ",
        "start": 101.052,
        "duration": 2.354
    },
    {
        "text": "using a slashing motion.",
        "start": 103.406,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "Once it is evenly moistened, ",
        "start": 110.207,
        "duration": 1.952
    },
    {
        "text": "put the dough into a large food storage bag.",
        "start": 112.159,
        "duration": 3.342
    },
    {
        "text": "Flatten the dough with your hands.",
        "start": 120.019,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, roll it into a 3mm (0.1”) thick sheet evenly ",
        "start": 125.001,
        "duration": 4.045
    },
    {
        "text": "using a rolling pin.",
        "start": 129.046,
        "duration": 2.102
    },
    {
        "text": "Run a finger along both sides of the bag ",
        "start": 133.486,
        "duration": 2.946
    },
    {
        "text": "so that you can easily cut the edges off later.",
        "start": 136.432,
        "duration": 3.668
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, the cookie dough has firmed up.",
        "start": 147.241,
        "duration": 2.884
    },
    {
        "text": "Trim off both the left and right edges of the bag.",
        "start": 151.183,
        "duration": 3.717
    },
    {
        "text": "Peel off the plastic.",
        "start": 159.525,
        "duration": 1.906
    },
    {
        "text": "Coat the pastry cutter with flour ",
        "start": 165.816,
        "duration": 2.451
    },
    {
        "text": "and divide the sheet into rectangular pieces.",
        "start": 168.267,
        "duration": 3.568
    },
    {
        "text": "Like shown, mark the grid pattern on the sheet ",
        "start": 173.503,
        "duration": 3.102
    },
    {
        "text": "so that you can easily cut it into equal pieces.",
        "start": 176.605,
        "duration": 4.235
    },
    {
        "text": "Trim off the edges of the dough.",
        "start": 184.545,
        "duration": 2.497
    },
    {
        "text": "The size of each cookie is 8.5cm by 2.5cm (3.3”x1”) ",
        "start": 190.929,
        "duration": 6.117
    },
    {
        "text": "and you’ll get 18 pieces from the sheet in total.",
        "start": 197.046,
        "duration": 4.369
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, using a kitchen brush, ",
        "start": 205.218,
        "duration": 2.335
    },
    {
        "text": "coat the top of the dough with the beaten egg.",
        "start": 207.553,
        "duration": 3.25
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, place 3 almond slices on top of each piece.",
        "start": 217.206,
        "duration": 4.475
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the cookies onto a baking sheet ",
        "start": 228.712,
        "duration": 2.452
    },
    {
        "text": "covered with parchment paper.",
        "start": 231.164,
        "duration": 2.532
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, coat your hands with flour.",
        "start": 238.933,
        "duration": 2.786
    },
    {
        "text": "Gather the leftover dough ",
        "start": 242.585,
        "duration": 2.133
    },
    {
        "text": "and shape it into a flat circle.",
        "start": 246.417,
        "duration": 2.882
    },
    {
        "text": "Coat a poodle-shaped cutter with flour ",
        "start": 250.884,
        "duration": 2.802
    },
    {
        "text": "and then cut out the dough.",
        "start": 253.686,
        "duration": 2.065
    },
    {
        "text": "If the dough is too soft to shape, ",
        "start": 257.227,
        "duration": 2.377
    },
    {
        "text": "chill it in the fridge or freezer to harden.",
        "start": 259.604,
        "duration": 3.318
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the poodle-shaped dough onto the baking sheet.",
        "start": 264.34,
        "duration": 3.787
    },
    {
        "text": "And coat it with the beaten egg.",
        "start": 269.943,
        "duration": 2.652
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the baking sheet into the oven.",
        "start": 277.881,
        "duration": 2.635
    },
    {
        "text": "Bake the cookies at 160°C (320°F) for about 11 minutes.",
        "start": 282.002,
        "duration": 6.235
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, they’re ready.",
        "start": 292.293,
        "duration": 1.902
    },
    {
        "text": "Remove the almond cookies from the oven.",
        "start": 294.765,
        "duration": 3.036
    },
    {
        "text": "Mmmmm.",
        "start": 298.883,
        "duration": 1.437
    },
    {
        "text": "They smell so good!",
        "start": 300.32,
        "duration": 2.218
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the cookies onto a cooling rack.",
        "start": 303.206,
        "duration": 3.152
    },
    {
        "text": "When the baking sheet is cooled, ",
        "start": 306.807,
        "duration": 1.983
    },
    {
        "text": "you can bake the rest of the cookie dough as well.",
        "start": 308.79,
        "duration": 3.386
    },
    {
        "text": "These almond cookies are relatively thin ",
        "start": 312.792,
        "duration": 2.819
    },
    {
        "text": "and they are perfect for making cookie sandwiches.",
        "start": 315.611,
        "duration": 3.612
    },
    {
        "text": "We’re planning to make ",
        "start": 319.223,
        "duration": 1.252
    },
    {
        "text": "popular Raisin Sandwhich Cookies in the future.",
        "start": 320.475,
        "duration": 3.666
    },
    {
        "text": "We recommend using the extra fine sugar ",
        "start": 333.852,
        "duration": 2.646
    },
    {
        "text": "to help it combine with the butter.",
        "start": 336.498,
        "duration": 2.967
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 339.465,
        "duration": 1.614
    }
]